## Detailed Phase Breakdown

### Phase 1: Critical Bugs & Security Fixes
- **Auth Caching (BUG-1)**: Implemented `userCache` using `node-cache` with a 5-minute TTL in `authMiddleware.js`, reducing database lookup overhead on every authenticated API call.
- **Socket Dashboard Debounce (BUG-3)**: Implemented debouncing on incoming real-time socket events (`invalidate_dashboard`) in frontend hook `useSocket.ts` to prevent UI thrashing.
- **Duplicate Notifications (BUG-4)**: Cleaned up duplicate notification widgets and fixed rendering logic in `Header.tsx`.
- **Overdue Fee Logic (BUG-6)**: Corrected fee transaction filtering logic to accurately evaluate overdue balances against correct timestamps.
- **Relative Timestamps (BUG-7)**: Fixed negative relative timestamp rendering in `formatRelativeTime` helper.
- **Rate Limiting (SEC-2)**: Enabled strict IP-based rate limiting globally and applied exponential backoff brute-force protection to `/auth/login`.
- **Strong Credential Policies (SEC-4 & SEC-5)**: Enforced strict password complexity rules (min 8 chars, uppercase, number, special char) across registration and password resets.
- **Error Stack Traces (SEC-6)**: Completely sanitized error responses in `errorHandler.js`, ensuring stack traces are never leaked in production environments.

### Phase 2: Performance & Scalability
- **Dashboard Cache Layer (BUG-2 & PERF-5)**: Built a comprehensive, multi-layered Redis/in-memory caching system in `dashboardController.js` with role-specific cache keys and background invalidation.
- **DB-Level Pagination (BUG-5 & PERF-3)**: Upgraded fee transactions and report card endpoints to utilize database-level `take` and `skip` pagination rather than loading full datasets into memory.
- **Batched Queries (PERF-1)**: Re-architected monthly fee aggregation to utilize batched Prisma queries, drastically improving query performance.
- **Inventory Filtering (PERF-2)**: Shifted low-stock item filtering from JavaScript memory filtering to efficient SQL/Prisma `where: { quantity: { lte: minStock } }` queries.
- **O(1) Map Lookups (PERF-4)**: Refactored attendance processing algorithms from O(N²) nested array iterations to lightning-fast O(1) JavaScript `Map` lookups.
- **Role-Based Code Splitting (PERF-6)**: Implemented dynamic component loading in React using `React.lazy` and `Suspense` for role-specific dashboard views.
- **UI Notifications (PERF-7)**: Replaced intrusive blocking `alert()` dialogues with polished, non-blocking toast notifications.

### Phase 3: Architectural Refactoring & Code Quality
- **Controller-Service-Repository Pattern (CQ-1 & CQ-2)**: Completely decoupled business logic from Express route controllers by engineering dedicated `UserService.js`, `UserRepository.js`, `TimetableService.js`, `TermService.js`, and `TermRepository.js` classes.
- **TypeScript Strictness (CQ-3)**: Audited frontend API clients and eliminated loose `any` types in favor of strict interfaces.
- **Standardized Error Handling (CQ-4)**: Upgraded `AppError.js` and `errorHandler.js` to support structured validation error details (`err.errors`) for seamless API consumer integration.
- **File Naming & Import Order (CQ-5 & CQ-7)**: Standardized file naming conventions across the project and resolved bottom-of-file/mid-file import ordering anomalies.

### Phase 4: Advanced Security Hardening
- **Refresh Token System (SEC-1)**: Created `RefreshToken` model in Prisma schema, pushed to PostgreSQL, and implemented short-lived JWT access tokens (15m) paired with cryptographically secure refresh token rotation (7d) and automatic reuse detection/revocation.
- **Comprehensive Route Validation (SEC-7)**: Applied rigorous Zod validation middleware (`validate`) across auth, user management, and fee endpoints.
- **Secure File Uploads (SEC-8 & 4.3)**: Engineered a centralized `fileUpload.js` utility that enforces strict MIME type filtering, file size ceilings (5MB/10MB), and cryptographically randomized filenames preventing directory traversal vulnerabilities.

### Phase 5: Production Infrastructure
- **Deep Health Check (5.1)**: Built `/health` and `/api/health` endpoints returning database ping latency, memory consumption (RSS/Heap), uptime, and BullMQ queue statuses.
- **Graceful Shutdown (5.2)**: Configured robust `SIGINT` and `SIGTERM` trap handlers in `index.js` to cleanly close HTTP ports, flush BullMQ worker jobs, and disconnect Prisma connection pools.
- **API Versioning (5.3)**: Implemented `/api/v1` versioned routers alongside backward-compatible legacy routes.
- **Production React Query (5.4)**: Configured TanStack React Query in `QueryProvider.tsx` with optimized `staleTime` (5m), `gcTime` (15m), and exponential backoff retry logic.
- **Structured Request Logging (5.5)**: Integrated Morgan HTTP logging directly into Winston daily rotating JSON file streams (`logs/http-%DATE%.log`).
- **Financial Audit Logging (5.6)**: Created dedicated `auditLogger.js` middleware to record all sensitive fee, refund, and payment transactions into compliance-ready audit logs (`logs/audit-%DATE%.log`) with auto-sanitized card numbers and passwords.

### Phase 6: Automated Testing & Verification
- **Unit Testing (6.1)**: Engineered robust Jest unit test suites (`auth.test.js` and `fees.test.js`) verifying JWT issuing, password bcrypt hashing, strong password policies, and fee structure/payment validations.
- **Integration Testing (6.2)**: Built Express Supertest integration test suites (`integration.test.js`) verifying complete auth login flows and deep health check responses.
